Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on cache-enabled heterogeneous networks and investigates the optimal caching policy to maximize success probability and area spectral efficiency. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry theory to derive the success probability and ASE, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and transmission rates.
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper may also fall under the domain of game theory as it involves optimizing caching policies to maximize success probability and ASE, which can be viewed as a game between the network nodes.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may also involve systems and control as it deals with optimizing the performance of a complex network system.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may also involve multimedia as it deals with optimizing the delivery of multimedia content in a cache-enabled network.
